info.name: Launch For Integrators Pricing Example
info.description:
**Overview**

This collection contains folders containing two examples. The 1st is the existing L4I functionality, where an integrator requests a link for a new merchant and does not specify a pricing plan. In this case, a preconfigured pricing template will be used to generate the pricing plan for the merchant. The 2nd is the new L4I functionality, where the integrator retrieves a pricing template and constructs a pricing plan that fits within its parameters. The integrator then includes the pricing plan when they request a link for the new merchant.

---

**Security**

Each request should include the following headers in order to pass security:

AccessKey: {Access Key}

MerchantId: {Merchant ID}

The MerchantID sent in the header should match the one that is used in the URL on each of the requests sent in this collection. If you set the variables in the Variables tab for this folder, the requests in the nested folders should use those values.

item.name: Custom Pricing Plan

exec: //Choose an available Pricing Plan Template to use.

request.description: The options available in the Pricing API may differ based on the integrator and can be retrieved from the PricingPlanTemplate/All endpoint as a PricingPlanTemplate. We recommend dynamically constructing a PricingPlan for your merchant based on the options returned to you from this endpoint. As an example, this request retrieves the a PricingPlanTemplate, the accompanying test maps the values from the PricingPlanTemplate into a PricingPlan, and then the following request sends that PricingPlan back.
